@startuml
title WebSocket por Salas - Componentes (estado atual + arquitetura alvo)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

package "Backend (atual)" {
  component "API HTTP de teste\n/health /rooms /ws/broadcast" as TestAPI
  component "lobbyStore (memória)" as Store

  component "WebSocketHandler\n(/ws)" as WSHandler
  component "Hub" as Hub
  component "RoomHub" as RoomHub
  component "Client" as Client

  component "WebSocketObserver\n(opcional)" as WSObserver
  component "EventBus\n(stub)" as EventBus
}

package "Clientes" {
  component "Frontend / Navegador" as Browser
}

Browser --> WSHandler : HTTP Upgrade
WSHandler --> Hub : AddClient(roomID, client)
Hub --> RoomHub : obter/criar sala + encaminhar
RoomHub --> Client : distribuição do payload (fan-out)
Client --> Browser : frames WebSocket

TestAPI --> Store : listar/entrar/sair de salas
TestAPI --> Hub : BroadcastToRoom(roomID, payload)

EventBus ..> WSObserver : notificar(event)
WSObserver ..> Hub : BroadcastToRoom(roomID, payload)

note right of Hub
Ponto único de entrada para encaminhamento
de mensagens por sala.

Remove o RoomHub quando a sala fica vazia
(após desconexão do último cliente).
end note

@enduml